# Industrial Crane Load & Collision Safety Guard (PIC18F4580) 🏗️⚠️

## 💡 Overview
This repository contains a hands-on system integration solution for an **Industrial Crane Hoisting Safety System** built on the **PIC18F4580** microcontroller. The project targets structural load preemption and physical collision avoidance by combining analog input scaling, multi-state visual/acoustic alerting, and high-priority hardware interrupt routines.

> 📊 **Educational Purpose:** This project is engineered as a design challenge following the hardware-software co-design principles of the APJ Abdul Kalam Technological University (KTU) Embedded Systems framework. It demonstrates real-time bare-metal safety monitoring without relying on third-party libraries.

---

## 🛠️ Hardware Requirements
* **Microcontroller:** PIC18F4580
* **Display:** 16x2 Character LCD (HD44780 compliant)
* **Sensors & Inputs:**
    * 10kΩ Linear Potentiometer (Simulating Crane Cable Load Cell)
    * Momentary Push Button / Limit Switch (Carriage Bumper Switch)
    * Momentary Push Button (System Reset Switch)
* **Actuators & Indicators:**
    * DC Motor with L293D Driver IC (or Relay Interface) for Hoist Control
    * 3x LEDs (Green, Yellow, Red) for Status Signaling
    * 5V Active Piezo Buzzer
* **Passives:** 10kΩ Resistors for active-low digital switch pull-ups.

---

## 📌 Pin Assignment & Hardware Architecture
To successfully deploy this firmware, the PIC18F4580 register configurations must map directly to the physical silicon layout. Below is the implemented architectural mapping:

| Hardware Link | Peripheral Functionality | Selected PIC18F4580 Pin | Type | Notes |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Load Potentiometer** | ADC Channel 0 (`AN0`) | `RA0` (Pin 2) | Analog Input | Reads 0V to 5V variable load voltage |
| **Bumper Limit Switch** | External Interrupt 0 (`INT0`) | `RB0` (Pin 33) | Digital Input | Edge-triggered hardware override |
| **Reset Push Button** | GPIO Input | `RD0` (Pin 19) | Digital Input | Monitored to exit locked collision state |
| **Hoist Motor Enable** | GPIO Output | `RD1` (Pin 20) | Digital Output | High = Motor Run, Low = Forced Brake |
| **Status LEDs & Buzzer** | GPIO Group | `RD2, RD3, RD4, RD5` | Digital Output | Drives Green, Yellow, Red LEDs & Buzzer |
| **LCD Data Bus** | 8-Bit Parallel | `PORTC` (`RC0–RC7`) | Digital Output | Sends command and character ASCII bytes |
| **LCD Control Lines** | RS / EN Strobe | `RA1` / `RA2` | Digital Output | Coordinates LCD latching protocols |

